President Obama expresses his support and admiration for the beatification of Archbishop Oscar Romero. He describes Archbishop Romero as an inspiration for people in El Salvador and across the Americas, noting his courage and perseverance in the face of opposition. The President highlights Archbishop Romero's commitment to the needs of the poor and oppressed, and how he fearlessly confronted the injustices he witnessed. He also acknowledges the progress made in El Salvador over the years but recognizes that there is still more to be done. The President emphasizes that the United States is guided by Archbishop Romero's vision in its efforts to promote economic opportunity, strengthen the rule of law, and create safer communities in Central America. He expresses gratitude to Pope Francis for his leadership and decision to beatify Archbishop Romero, and hopes that his vision can inspire respect for human dignity and the pursuit of justice and peace.